---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const aboutSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "name": "About PrivacyComply",
  "url": "https://privacycomply.io/about.html",
  "publisher": {"@type":"Organization","name":"PrivacyComply","url":"https://privacycomply.io/"}
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About PrivacyComply — Editorial Standards & Affiliate Disclosure"
  description="Who runs PrivacyComply, how we evaluate the tools we review, how we make money, and the editorial standards we hold ourselves to."
  canonical="/about.html"
>
  <Fragment slot="schema">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(aboutSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="article-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a><span>›</span> About</p>
      <h1>About PrivacyComply</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span>📅 Updated June 5, 2026</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="article">

    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>PrivacyComply publishes independent reviews and plain-English guides for data privacy compliance tools — cookie consent banners, GDPR software, CCPA solutions, and privacy policy generators. We exist for the people who actually have to ship the website and need a clear answer faster than reading 99 articles of regulatory text.</p>

    <h2>Who runs the site</h2>
    <p>PrivacyComply is operated by <strong>Strandway Ventures</strong>, a digital holding company based in Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, Canada. Strandway Ventures runs a portfolio of internet properties across travel, niche affiliate, lead generation, and B2B SaaS review verticals. Contact the editorial team at <code>hello@privacycomply.io</code>.</p>

    <h2>What we use ourselves</h2>
    <p>PrivacyComply practises what it covers. The compliance stack on this site is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cookie banner &amp; consent database:</strong> <a href="https://www.iubenda.com/" rel="noopener sponsored">iubenda</a> Privacy Controls and Cookie Solution — the banner you see in the corner is iubenda's, and every consent event is logged in iubenda's Consent Database.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy policy, cookie policy, terms &amp; conditions:</strong> Generated and hosted by iubenda. The authoritative versions live at <a href="/privacy-policy.html">privacy-policy.html</a>, <a href="/cookie-policy.html">cookie-policy.html</a>, and <a href="/terms.html">terms.html</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Google Analytics 4 with IP anonymisation, loaded only after consent.</li>
      <li><strong>Hosting &amp; framework:</strong> Astro static site deployed via GitHub Actions to Hostinger.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>That means when we review iubenda, we're reviewing a vendor we actually use — not one we read about. We disclose this in the iubenda comparison article and anywhere else it's relevant.</p>

    <h2>How we evaluate tools</h2>
    <p>We combine three signals when we assess a compliance vendor:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Hands-on use where we have it.</strong> iubenda is the clearest example — we run it on this site and on other Strandway Ventures properties, so the iubenda assessments reflect real operating experience.</li>
      <li><strong>Vendor documentation, pricing pages, and changelogs.</strong> We read every tier carefully so the comparison reflects what's actually included, not what's marketed.</li>
      <li><strong>Independent reporting and user discussion.</strong> G2, Capterra, Trustpilot, Reddit (r/SaaS, r/smallbusiness, r/gdpr), and product-hunt threads. We weight verified-user reviews higher than vendor case studies.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Where we have not personally deployed a tool, we say so. Reviews are re-checked at least quarterly because compliance vendors change pricing and features often.</p>

    <h2 id="disclosure">Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>PrivacyComply is reader-supported. Some of the links on this site are <strong>affiliate links</strong>, which means if you click through and sign up for a paid plan, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you.</p>
    <p>We currently have or are pursuing affiliate relationships with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>CookieYes</strong> — recurring commission program</li>
      <li><strong>iubenda</strong> — referral commission program</li>
      <li><strong>Termly</strong> — referral commission program</li>
      <li><strong>NordLayer</strong> — per-sale commission program</li>
      <li><strong>Osano</strong> — referral partner program (where available)</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Our editorial integrity rules:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Commission size never influences ranking. The ordering of "best tool" comparisons is based purely on the evaluation methodology above.</li>
      <li>We will not recommend a product we wouldn't install on our own sites.</li>
      <li>Every page that includes affiliate links carries a visible disclosure at the top of the page, not buried in a footer.</li>
      <li>If a tool changes for the worse — pricing hikes, feature removal, support degradation — we will say so even when it costs us commission.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="privacy">Privacy policy</h2>
    <p>Our full privacy policy is on a dedicated page: <a href="/privacy-policy.html">PrivacyComply Privacy Policy</a>. Short version: standard Google Analytics 4 (IP anonymisation on), CookieYes cookie banner, no selling visitor data. Privacy requests: <code>privacy@privacycomply.io</code>.</p>

    <h2>Editorial corrections</h2>
    <p>If you find a factual error in any of our reviews or guides, email <code>corrections@privacycomply.io</code>. We re-publish with a date-stamped correction note at the top of the affected article, and we credit the reader who flagged it (unless they prefer to remain anonymous).</p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not give legal advice. Our guides explain the law in plain language so you can make informed decisions, but for a compliance audit or a specific legal situation, hire a qualified data protection lawyer in your jurisdiction.</li>
      <li>We do not accept paid placement in our "best of" rankings. The ordering reflects our evaluation, not vendor relationships.</li>
      <li>We do not write fake reviews. Every product we cover is one we've either used ourselves or one whose coverage is based on vendor documentation and verified-user reviews — and we mark which is which.</li>
    </ul>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
